     `qx,qy` as 4-byte ints (2×12 MB) plus a 3 MB char array, and a 3 MB bool[3] table, pushes the working set beyond L2/L3 cache capacity. The resulting cache misses and TLB thrashing substantially slow down the neighbor-exploration loop.  
